<emphasis id="B9125561363D151FFF2C9F64FE8EFBDA" bold="true" box="[151,275,1059,1083]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C66F2F0363D151FFEA29F64FDDFFBDA" authority="Wu, 1948" authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="1948" box="[281,578,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Claassenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="B9125561363D151FFEA29F64FE48FBDA" box="[281,469,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Claassenia magna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF7F482363D151FFE679F63FDDFFBDA" author="Wu, C. F." box="[476,578,1059,1083]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="145 - 151" refId="ref3288" refString="Wu, C. F. (1948) Fifth supplement to the stoneflies of China (Order Plecoptera). Bulletin of the Peking Society of Natural History, 17 (2), 145 - 151." type="journal article" year="1948">Wu, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A. Male terminalia, dorsal view; B. Male tergum 8-10, details; C. Male hemitergum and cercal base, lateral view; D. Male terminalia, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF19D9FB363D151FFF2C9C93FBF6F80D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592809" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6592809" box="[151,1131,2004,2028]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592809/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" startId="3.[151,250,2004,2028]" targetBox="[164,1424,1144,1981]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BD98973363D151FFF2C9C93FBF6F80D" blockId="3.[151,1131,2004,2028]" box="[151,1131,2004,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">
<emphasis id="B9125561363D151FFF2C9C93FE8EF80D" bold="true" box="[151,275,2004,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C66F2F0363D151FFEA29C93FDDFF80D" authority="Wu, 1948" authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="1948" box="[281,578,2004,2028]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Claassenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="B9125561363D151FFEA29C93FE48F80D" box="[281,469,2004,2028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="290">Claassenia magna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF7F482363D151FFE679C92FDDFF80D" author="Wu, C. F." box="[476,578,2004,2028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="290" pagination="145 - 151" refId="ref3288" refString="Wu, C. F. (1948) Fifth supplement to the stoneflies of China (Order Plecoptera). Bulletin of the Peking Society of Natural History, 17 (2), 145 - 151." type="journal article" year="1948">Wu, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B. Aedeagus, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD98973363A1518FF7C9BD0FF64FF18" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,466]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
Aedeagus membranous, without any conspicuous lobes or spines, long cylinder, the base is simple, ventrally middle of aedeagus inflated to slightly spherical, both dorsally and ventrally the end slender and pointed (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363A1518FADF9BFCFF71FF18" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[151,250,2004,2028]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,1144,1981]" captionTargetId="figure-174@3.[164,1424,1144,1981]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B. Aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592809/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Figs. 4A‒4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD98973363A1518FF7C9A44FCF5FE33" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,466]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis id="B9125561363A1518FF7C9A44FE83FEFC" bold="true" box="[199,286,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Female</emphasis>
. Forewing length 
<quantity id="4C9E2496363A1518FE539A44FDD0FEFC" box="[488,589,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.96" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="39.6">39.6 mm</quantity>
, hindwing length 
<quantity id="4C9E2496363A1518FCA89A44FCE5FEFC" box="[787,888,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6399999999999997" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="36.4">36.4 mm</quantity>
, body length 
<quantity id="4C9E2496363A1518FBB69A44FBEDFEFC" box="[1037,1136,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.18" pageId="4" pageNumber="291" unit="mm" value="41.8">41.8 mm</quantity>
(n = 1), general body color darker than males but pattern similar to males (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363A1518FD109A60FD6DFEA0" box="[683,752,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1110,1134]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,489,1087]" captionTargetId="figure-164@4.[153,1435,489,1087]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. Female adult, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592812/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Pronotum is similar in shape to males, margins and middle longitudinal line dark brown (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363A1518FE5F9A0CFDA0FE87" box="[484,573,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1685,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. A. Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. Female terminalia, dorsal view; C. Female terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592814/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Terga 9 
<emphasis id="B9125561363A1518FD1F9A0CFD2FFE84" bold="true" box="[676,690,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">–</emphasis>
10 dark brown, tergum 10 with triangular posterior projection (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363A1518FAD49A0CFF21FE6B" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1685,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. A. Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. Female terminalia, dorsal view; C. Female terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592814/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 8 with slight extension, subgenital plate broad and slightly protruded posteromedially, dense hairs on sternum 8, sternum 9 humped medially, the internode membrane of sterna 9 and 10 with a dense band of hairs, sternum 10 mostly pale, posterolateral margins brown (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363A1518FCB99AF0FCC6FE33" box="[770,859,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1685,1709]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetId="figure-177@4.[151,1436,1158,1661]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 6. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. A. Female head and pronotum, dorsal view; B. Female terminalia, dorsal view; C. Female terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592814/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="291">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
