<subSubSection id="C37CDAF8363B1519FF7C9BFCFCA8FE68" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD98973363B1519FF7C9BFCFCA8FE68" blockId="5.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis id="B9125561363B1519FF7C9BFCFEA6FF34" bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens that were collected at the type locality (Wuyi Mountain, 
<collectingRegion id="49A24791363B1519FB399BFCFAA5FF37" box="[1154,1336,187,214]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Fujian Province</collectingRegion>
) and the male described above are identical to the 
<typeStatus id="54DD37D1363B1519FDCE9B98FD4AFF18" box="[629,727,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F2F0363B1519FCBB9B98FCF2FF19" authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="1948" box="[768,879,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Claassenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="B9125561363B1519FCBB9B98FCF2FF19" box="[768,879,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">C. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all with a small group of sensilla basiconica on tergum 8 and a larger oval patch of sensilla basiconica on tergum 9 (
<figureCitation id="135D95F6363B1519FC049A44FBCBFEFC" box="[959,1110,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1059,1083]" captionTargetBox="[159,1409,418,1036]" captionTargetId="figure-142@3.[159,1428,417,1036]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Claassenia magna Wu, 1948. A. Male terminalia, dorsal view; B. Male tergum 8-10, details; C. Male hemitergum and cercal base, lateral view; D. Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592807" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592807/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Figs. 3A‒3B</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF7F482363B1519FBD69A44FB79FEFC" author="Du, Y. Z." box="[1133,1252,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" refId="ref2871" refString="Du, Y. Z. (1999) A taxonomic study on Plecoptera from China. Unpublished Postdoctoral Dissertation, Zhejiang University, Hangzhou, 324 pp." type="book" year="1999">Du (1999)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the males based on specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion id="49A24791363B1519FDD49A60FCB0FEA0" box="[623,813,295,321]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Guangxi Zhuang</collectingRegion>
Autonomous Region. In this study, we also examined a series from Nanling National Forest Park and Mangshan National Forest Park, which is close to 
<collectingRegion id="49A24791363B1519FB609A0CFAA3FE84" box="[1243,1342,331,357]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, and the morphological characteristics are consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F2F0363B1519FD799A28FCB3FE69" authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="1948" box="[706,814,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Claassenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis id="B9125561363B1519FD799A28FCB3FE69" box="[706,814,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">C. magna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
